title: Mount Tate (New South Wales)
text:
Mount Tate is a prominent rocky <a href="mountain">mountain</a> on the <a href="Main%20Range%20%28Snowy%20Mountains%29">Main Range</a> of the <a href="Snowy%20Mountains">Snowy Mountains</a> located in southeastern <a href="New%20South%20Wales">New South Wales</a>, <a href="Australia">Australia</a>.
With an elevation of <a href="Australian%20Height%20Datum">above sea level</a>, Mount Tate has two ridges running north and south, named Tate West Ridge and Tate East Ridge, referring to the side of the <a href="Great%20Dividing%20Range">Great Divide</a> where they lie. It has views along the Main Range towards <a href="Mount%20Twynam">Mount Twynam</a> and down to the <a href="Geehi%20River">Geehi Valley</a>.
The mountain is situated approximately northeast of <a href="Guthega%2C%20New%20South%20Wales">Guthega</a> and southwest of <a href="Guthega%20Power%20Station">Guthega Power Station</a>.
